Why Blockchain? 

The basic idea behind the GAT System is to provide users the opportunity to trade Merchant Tokens with 

one another and to exchange them for goods and services from the respective merchants. The systems needs 

to be able to do this in a frictionless, yet verifiably secure way. As the Merchant Tokens will have real value 

it is important that it will not be able to copy or double spend them. Another requirement is that Merchant 

Tokens should have the ability, if the merchant chooses so, to create verifiably unique and rare tokens. 

Blockchain technology, and its successors, provide the solution to create a system which fulfills these 

requirements. 

 

People will need to be able to exchange the Merchant Tokens with a common medium of exchange. This 

medium of exchange is GAT. Besides being able to trade Merchant Tokens into and out of GAT, holding 

GAT gives users extra functionality like being able to receive special Merchant Tokens or GATCOIN 

promotions using the A-DropTM technology. The GAT System also provides merchants value in the form 

of collected metadata and making these available for them in exchange for GAT, while also doing this in a 

verifiably secure, frictionless way where it is possible to see the non-reissuable circulating supply of tokens. 

Users will know they are the true owners of these coins and the only ones able to spend them, when they 

hold the keys in their wallets. Blockchains, such as Ethereum for GAT and private blockchains for Merchant 

Tokens, fulfill all these requirements, while also making it possible to create a completely Decentralised 

Exchange, or DEX, at a later stage. 

  

